The paper discusses the security concerns and challenges in designing autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also emphasizes the need for a security-by-design framework, which involves software engineering principles (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI) for developing secure autonomous systems. The paper also discusses the interaction of autonomous vehicles with other smart systems, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
